{
  "stem": "18778.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 316.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My personal opinion, my very personal opinion is that everything was already prearranged with the Cubans way ahead of time, that no matter what the Cubans would not allow us to land, and send us back to no man's land or wherever, and to see whether the world would open up its countries and take these few people in who were all skilled people, either in the professions or in the trades, and see what kind of world reaction there would be.",
      "word_count": 82
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were a handful, perhaps six or eight passengers, who had absolutely legal immigration permits, who were allowed to disembark, including two children whose father was in Cuba, whose Aryan mother didn't want her Jewish children anymore, and shipped them out of Germany to their father in Cuba.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know who the other people were.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of them may have been Cuban citizens.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whoever they were, they must have had very legal papers and they were able to get off the ship.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I don't think there were 10.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think it was less than 10 people who got off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had connections in Cuba through these Cuban friends that my parents had made in [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Bun, ?] who could have gotten us off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father, as the chairman of the committee, said he cannot do that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He cannot leave the committee.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He cannot leave everybody in the lurch, and he will not do it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so we stayed on the ship.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He also felt he would endanger our lives if we tried to get off the ship.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So that was just a moot point.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The next day, after loading provisions, the ship left.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
